judgment_text:
IN THE HIGH COURT OF JUDICATURE AT BOMBAY ORDINARY ORIGINAL CIVIL JURISDICGTION Contempt Petition No. 77 of 2004 in Writ Petition No. 1074 of 1987 Balasaheb P. Pawar ... Petitioner vs. The Airport Director, International Airport Authority of India & ors. .. Respondents Ms. Madhulata Rajale i/b Mahesh Thorat for petitioner Mr. S.K. Talsania with Yastal Mehta i/b. Kanga & Girdharilal for respondent CORAM: A. S. AGUIAR J. Date: December, 17, 2004 P.C.

Learned advocate for the respondent files affidavit in reply to show cause notice dated 3rd November 2004 from which it appears that the respondents have substantially complied with the order dated 3rd September 2003 and the consequential reliefs prayed for are under consideration. However, for quantifying the consequential reliefs he requires certain information to be supplied by the petitioner. The petitioner is directed to supply the necessary information to the respondents within a week. S. O. beyond x-mas vacation. (A. S. AGUIAR J.)
